      "name": "What does 'going unconditional' mean in a Queensland property sale?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "A property sale goes unconditional when all conditions in the contract, typically finance approval and building and pest inspection, have been satisfied or waived by the buyer. At that point the contract becomes binding on both parties. The seller is committed to selling, and the buyer is committed to completing the purchase at the agreed price on the agreed settlement date. There is no further right of termination based on those conditions once they have been satisfied or waived."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can a seller keep the deposit if a buyer defaults after going unconditional in Queensland?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. If a buyer defaults after the contract has gone unconditional, the seller's primary remedy is to serve a notice to complete and, if the buyer still fails to settle, terminate the contract and forfeit the deposit. Under the standard REIQ contract, the deposit is released to the seller upon termination for buyer default. If the eventual resale price is lower than the original contract price, the seller may also sue for the difference in damages, less the deposit already forfeited."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What should a seller do immediately when a buyer signals they cannot settle after going unconditional?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Contact your property solicitor immediately. Do not agree to any informal extension without getting legal advice first, and do not agree to vary the contract verbally. Your solicitor will advise whether to issue a notice to complete and the correct form and timing for doing so. Any informal extension that is not properly documented can affect your legal position. Acting promptly protects your right to forfeit the deposit and pursue damages."
      }
    }
  ]
